product_name: Pai Skincare Light Work Rosehip Cleansing Oil 100ml
ingredients:
Pai Skincare’s delicate cleansing oil works to gently cleanse and refresh your complexion, effectively lifting away dirt and build-ups without stripping it of essential moisture. The formula is suitable for using on even sensitive skin and eyes, but will make light work of stubborn SPF, makeup and grime, promoting a softer, cleaner surface without any stinging. There’s no need to rub, making the whole process a smooth process from start to finish,

Formulated using Rosehip Fruit Extract, the cleanser leaves your skin with a radiant, natural-looking glow. It’s full of nourishing Omegas 3, 6 and 9, which come together to support normal repair cycles while Carotenoids offer protection against external damage with their antioxidant properties.

product_name: ClarityRx Balm It Off Nutrient Rich Pre-Cleanse 3 oz
ingredients:
Scoop balm. Warm the balm between your fingertips until it melts into an oil. Gently massage balm onto dry skin in circular motions. Rinse with lukewarm water or wipe off with a damp washcloth. Pat skin dry. For eye makeup removal, apply to a closed eye,
  • Safflower Oil – rich in antioxidants and essential fatty acids, this soothing, noncomedogenic oil helps to minimize the appearance of aging and prevent dry, rough skin promoting a smoother and softer appearance.
  • Sunflower Oil – beneficial for dry, dehydrated, or environmentally compromised skin, its linoleic acid content helps skin synthesize its own lipids, visibly repairing its barrier and leading to smoother skin.
  • Bergamot Oil – helps to cleanse the skin of surface oils and impurities.
  • Sweet Orange Oil – rich in Vitamin C, helps to cleanse the skin and even the complexion.
  • Vitamin E – powerful antioxidant helps to nourish and protect the skin from free-radical damage.
  • Shea Butter – Rich in omega-fatty acids, it effectively removes makeup & dirt while promoting elasticity, leaving skin feeling moisturized and smooth.

Ingredients: Caprylic/Capric Triglyceride (Vegetable Derived), Ethylhexyl Palmitate, Lauryl Laurate, Carthamus Tinctorius (Safflower) Seed Oil, Helianthus Annuus (Sunflower) Seed Oil,

product_name: Fillerina Labo Facial Lifting Cream - Grade 2 1.7 oz
ingredients: 1,6-Alpha–Linked Maltotriose is Pullulan (Pullulan is the INCI Name), a molecule that, just after the application on the skin, forms a network at skin surface that is responsible for the immediate shrinking and recompacting effect, with subsequent immediate lifting effect. However, Pullulan can also be absorbed by the skin and reach the dermis. Its absorption and the reaching of the dermis is promoted by 3 enhancers, belonging to the Patent on Labo Skin Technology No. 711 466, namely Pentylene Glycol, Decylene Glycol, Caprylyl Glycol. The Absorption Test conducted by means of Franz Cells (Report E. Ex07-MS04 2016/1896 dated 28/07/2016) showed an overall absorption percentage of Pullulan, in both epidermis and dermis, equal to 70.5%. The portion of Pullulan that reaches the dermis binds to dermal collagen forming a supporting scaffold that restores tissues' firmness and compactness for a long time. This is the “”mechanical”” effect in the medium and long term, which is added to the medium and long term effect performed by the molecules playing a dermo-cosmetic “”biological”” activity, that work synergistically on the structures of the dermis (Glycine, Proline, Alanine; Tripeptide-10 Citrulline; DMAE; 3-Aminopropane Sulfonic Acid; Acetyl Tetrapeptide-2).

product_name: PMD Personal Microderm Pro - White
ingredients:
1. Prior to using the PMD, it is important to thoroughly cleanse the skin, making sure that it is free from all make up, dirt, and oils. Once the skin is clean, allow it to dry completely before you begin.
2. Before using the tool on your face, practice on your arm and on your neck. These areas are not as sensitive as the face and will allow you to get used to motion and the way a treatment is performed.
3. Use the white disc first. This disc is our most sensitive disc. It is important to see how your skin responds to this disc before moving on to more abrasive discs.
4. After you have tested the unit on your arm and/or neck and feel ready to move on to your face, use a free hand to pull the skin tight in the treatment area and continue to move the PMD Personal Microderm in an upward motion across the skin. Do not make more than two passes over one area during the treatment.
5. Following the treatment, use a toner to neutralize the ph balance in the skin and a recovery moisturizer.
6. After each use, clean the cap and the disc with rubbing alcohol or an antibacterial soap.
7. Wait 6-7 days between treatments.

product_name: TriPollar STOP X ROSE Ombre
ingredients: Apply a very thin layer of the TriPollar Preparation Gel over the entire treatment area on the face. Divide the face into 3 treatment areas (Right Cheek, Left Cheek, Forehead). Turn the device ‘on’ by pressing the Power button. Place the device on the skin, make sure to apply a slight pressure in order to assure full contact between the electrodes and the skin. Move the device in a very slow circular motion on a small part of your treatment area, slowly heating your skin to the optimal temperature. Once the orange indicator light illuminates followed by a ‘beep’ sound, you have reached the optimal temperature. Continue the same slow circular motion for a few seconds, then gradually enlarge the movements in the treatment area. Continue working on the entire treatment area in slow circular motion for 4-5 minutes, and proceed to the next treatment area, repeating the above steps. Once complete, wash your face with warm water to remove the TriPollar Preparation Gel. Follow with your favorite serum and/or face cream.

product_name: Pai Skincare Viper's Gloss Echium and Amaranth Face Oil 30ml
ingredients:
Blended with ten different wonder oils, Pai Skincare’s face oil helps to revitalise complexions suffering from dullness. Ideal for dry or ageing skin types, the formula can even be used by those experiencing sensitivity or anyone prone to eczema. It’s a rich, concentrated blend that deeply nourishes the skin, helping to restore goodness that is lost through the ageing process,

Enriched with Echium, also known as Viper’s Bugloss, the oil contains potent Omegas 3 and 6 (Gamma Linolenic Acid and Stearidonic Acid). These work to smooth and perfect your complexion, helping to lessen the look of fine lines for a more youthful illusion. Thanks to Amaranth Oil, you’ll benefit from plenty of moisture that gives skin a softer, suppler appearance. This powerful botanical oil is also known as a natural form of squalene, which is produced by our own skin. It delivers impressive antioxidant protection to fight environmental aggressors.

A light, mattifying daily moisturiser to hydrate and control oil production,

Moisture Defence – Oily does all the things a good moisturiser should do, like hydrate and soften the skin. But it overachieves to ensure it doesn’t add excess oil to the skin or clog pores, both major concerns for oily skins and acne sufferers. In fact, this formula not only hydrates but it also gently exfoliates, helping to improve congestion and move dead skin cells along before they morph into blackheads and then acne.
